main event: Witnesses observed an unusually reddish-colored object slowly rise in the eastern sky near Knox City, Missouri on January 29, 1957.
interesting points: The object appeared a bit flat on the top and bottom as it climbed higher.
The witnesses could not determine the exact color of the object.
The object showed no light or sound.
The object appeared to be at a high altitude.
The witnesses concluded they had likely observed the moon rising in the eastern sky.
result: Explained - The witnesses likely observed the rising moon.
sighted object: A reddish-colored, flat-topped object in the sky
photographs: No, the report does not include any photographs
